Mara had always thought love was a grand, exaggerated thing—like a cloud that could swallow the whole sky, or a pillow that could hold the weight of the world. She loved her brother, Eli, but she kept his affection at arm’s length, convinced that real love had to be dramatic, thunderous, and larger than life.

